creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
inscription:
Signature, Date, Inscription, Stamps

inscribed in plate at upper left: [HERCVLIS]
markings: brown star-shaped stamp on verso, lower left, unidentified. Also on verso: loan number for 1941 Baltimore exhibition.
provenance: Collector with unidentified mark; David Tunick, New York; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
signed: monogram and date in plate at upper left: [1542 / HSB]
title: Hercules Killing Nessus, From the Labors of Hercules
